sysinv/sysinv/sysinv/sysinv/api/controll.message:
I just have two concerns:
@Kristine
1) The target growth size mentioned in the error message (cgtsvg_growth_gib) is calculated only based on the controller filesystems. If we remove the filesystem names, the error message would be "Target growth size XX exceeds growth limit XX". Wouldn't that be an unclear error message as the user is not aware how the growth is calculated? If yes, do you have suggestion for a better error message?

@Bart
2) When controllerfs-list command runs, the database size is shown as 10GB. However, internally the space allocated is 20GB. If we remove the individual names, the calculations can be a little mysterious for the user as they would not know that the database is doubled for upgrades. Currently, this is being reflected in the error message as follows:
"database (doubled for upgrades)".
